In order to form a limited partnership, a certificate of limited partnership shall be executed and filed with the Secretary of State. The certificate shall be in the form prescribed by the Secretary of State and shall set forth:
The name of the limited partnership;
The address of the office and the name and address of the agent for service of process required to be maintained by KRS 14A.4-010 or predecessor law;
The name and the business address of each general partner;
A mailing address for the limited partnership;
The latest date upon which the limited partnership is to dissolve; and
Any other matters the general partners determine to include therein.
